- AdColony: https://www.adcolony.com/privacy-policy/
- ByteDance
- Unity: https://unity3d.com/legal/privacy-policy
5.3. With public authorities in your country
In accordance with relevant laws, we may have to disclose your information to public authorities in your country, whenever such disclosure is deemed necessary for protecting, challenging or enforcing the legal rights of us, our users, or our partners. Unless required by law, we will not be required to notify you of any such disclosure.
6. Personal information security
We take reasonable security measures to protect your information from any alteration, loss, misuse or any unauthorized access as far as practically possible. We stringently request that our partners always act in compliance with information protection legislation applicable and grant special attention to confidentiality of this information.
But we do not warrant or represent that your information will be protected absolutely against alteration, loss, or misuse by third parties. And any method of transmission over the Internet is not secure absolutely. Please be careful of your security to use the Internet by yourselves.
7. Specific provisions for users under GDPR or the equivalents
7.1. Accessing and correcting your information
At any time, you may contact us at the address provided in the “Contact” section herein and request to access the personal information that we hold about you. We may need to ask you to provide certain information to make sure you are who you claim to be. If you find the information on your account is not accurate, complete or updated, then please provide us with the necessary information to correct it.
7.2. Withdrawing your consent
Whenever we rely on your consent, you have the right to withdraw that consent at any time.
Please contact us if you would like to withdraw your consent to the processing of your personal information. Exercising this right will not affect the lawfulness of processing based on consent before withdrawal.
7.3. Erasing or restricting access to your information
You may request to delete or restrict access to your personal information. We may postpone or deny your request if your information is in current use for providing services or for other legitimate purposes, in which case we will let you know why we are unable to do so.
7.4. Transferring your information (your right to data portability)
You have the right to receive your personal information that you have provided us in a structured, commonly used and machine readable format and the right to transmit that data to another party of your choice, where technically feasible. However, this right shall not apply where it would adversely affect the rights and freedoms of others.
7.5. Transfer of your information outside your country
We may transfer information that we collect about you to affiliated entities, or to other partners across borders and from your country or jurisdiction to other countries or jurisdictions around the world, including those located in the United States of America and Japan. Please note that these countries and jurisdictions may not have the same data protection laws as your own jurisdiction.
7.6. Data retention period
We retain your information for as long as needed to provide you services, unless we are required by law to delete or if we accept your request to delete the information. We will also retain and use your information as necessary to comply with our legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements.
7.7. Our policy regarding children
We do not knowingly collect or solicit personal information from anyone under the age of 16 or knowingly allow such persons to use our services. If you are under 16, please do not send any information about yourselves to us, including your name, address, telephone number, or email address. We are afraid to say that you must not use our services if you are under 16 years old.
7.8. Complaint to a supervisory authority
In accordance with Article 77 of the GDPR, you may also make a complaint to the Information Commissioner’s Office, or the data protection regulator in the country where you usually live or work, or where an alleged infringement of the GDPR has taken place.
8. Contact
You may contact our Data Protection Officer at funnycreator@163.com or the address below for further information.
Funny Creator
9. Changes to this policy
We may update this policy. We encourage you to check back frequently to see any updates or changes to this policy. Please note that if we need to adapt the policy to legal requirements, the new policy will become effective immediately or as required.
Effective Date: November 8, 2018